editorialNotes.short: Learn how to make healthier choices about the food you eat.

editorialNotes.standard: Bookend your days with a moment of reflection in stoic., an elegantly designed journaling app made for anyone looking to carve out time for mindfulness. With insightful reflection prompts and breathing exercises, the app is filled with multiple ways to care for your mental health—with inspiration from stoic philosophy at its core.
editorialNotes.short: Meet your daily companion for journaling, meditation and reflection.

editorialNotes.standard: Keeping the original’s streamlined interface, this version adds a wealth of new features. Enrich your journal entries with photos, location info, even fitness activity. And see your world at a glance with the beautiful photo view.
editorialNotes.short: Make retracing your steps a pleasure with this elegant notebook.

editorialNotes.standard: If you’re like us, you need all the help you can get turning rare quiet moments into true meditation. Headspace’s rich, accessible lessons gently explore how to improve mindfulness. Oh, and we love how Headspace’s Apple Watch app lets you hit a literal panic button when extra-stressful situations arise.
editorialNotes.short: Improve mindfulness with guided meditation lessons.

editorialNotes.standard: Robust insights let you set goals and savour moments of mindfulness, uncovering more about your virtual pet’s personality, as well as your own needs too.

Take a deep breath: it’s both a call to action and a defining feature of this app’s approach to meditation. In a crowded field of mindfulness apps, it stands out for its ease of use and attention to (soothing) detail.
editorialNotes.short: Try breathing techniques for quick relaxation.

editorialNotes.standard: This app started as a simple timer app for meditating, but it’s evolved into a comprehensive way to help people, while gaining insight along the way. With lessons which range from short to long and luxurious, it features thousands of guided meditations across a range of styles.
editorialNotes.short: Set a timer or relax with guided meditation sessions.

editorialNotes.standard: This app’s bite-size workouts don’t require a gym membership or special equipment. Best of all, you can launch these satisfying mini-routines right from Apple Watch – it’s like having a personal trainer right on your wrist.
editorialNotes.short: There are no excuses. It’s only seven minutes a day!
Achieve your fitness and wellness goals.
Calm yourself with elegant white noise and a focus timer.

editorialNotes.short: Calm down with personalised soundscapes.

editorialNotes.short: Stay hydrated every day with reminders to drink water.

editorialNotes.standard: Rather than yanking you from your slumber like an alarm clock, this app analyses your sleep patterns using your device’s microphone, then picks your lightest sleep to rouse you gently.
editorialNotes.short: Keep track of your sleeping habits and wake up feeling rested.

editorialNotes.standard: We love being able to create a full-body or targeted workout based on your skill level and what equipment you have on hand. Create your own routines by selecting the exercise and setting reps or duration.
editorialNotes.short: Start a workout with Siri on your iPhone, iPad and Apple Watch.

editorialNotes.standard: Want to break a sweat? Celebrity trainers like actor Gabrielle Union and Queer Eye guru Jonathan Van Ness guide you through challenging routines you can stream on demand, while FitOn’s core fitness team leads live classes nearly every hour of the day.

editorialNotes.standard: Not everyone has a yoga studio nearby for their downward-dog and warrior-pose fix, which is why Yoogaia brings the studio to you. Recorded sessions from studios across the world are always available, but the real fun is connecting with live classes from the comfort of your living room so instructors can offer feedback and encouragement. With its crisp design and smart search features, Yoogaia makes it easy to book sessions with your favourite yogi, letting you get limber without ever leaving home.

editorialNotes.standard: There’s nothing like a cute llama to help you track the liquids you consume. As you do, unlock a world of characters, tools and challenges to help you stay on top of your hydration goals.

editorialNotes.standard: Part immersive audio experience and part travel companion, this gorgeous app lets you focus, study or snooze in lush audio environments from all corners of the globe. Bonus: Pair some compatible AirPods to experience it all in spatial audio.

editorialNotes.standard: An invaluable tool for reaching your weight-loss goals, Lose It! tracks your meals, exercise, and nutrition. Documenting food is effortless with its built-in barcode scanner, searchable list of common grocery items, and database of popular restaurant meals’ nutritional facts. Plus, when you need some extra motivation, the app’s social features make it easy to find inspiration from friends and cheer each other on.
editorialNotes.short: Stay on track and monitor your daily calorie budget.
